#Building HTML Pages

The frontend uses Flask's templates/ for HTML pages and static for OSS/IS to provide a structured, user-friendly interface for the flood prediction model.

1. templates/ Folder (HTML Pages)

home.html Landing page explaining the project.

index.html Input form for weather parameters (sends data to backend).

chance.html: Alert page displayed if a flood is predicted.

nv_chance.html: Safe page displayed if no flood is predicted.

2. static/ Folder (Frontend Assets)

main.css Enhances visual design, layvut, and responsiveness.

main.js: Adds interactivity, form validation, and button actions.

Ovnclusivn: Separating HTML files and static assets ensures a well-organized, attractive, and easily manageable application.

