##Build the Python Script (app.py)

Setup and Initialization

Import Dependencies: Load the Flask module and joblib.

Initialize App: Create the application instance using Flask(name).

Load Assets: Lead the saved model (flowds.save) and scaler (transform.save) to process inputs and generate predictions.

Page Routing: URL endpoints are bound to HTML templates using the @app.route() decorator and render_template():

/ routes to home.html (Landing page).

Predict routes to index.html (Input form).

/chance routes to chance.html (Flowd predicted).

/nv_chance routes to no_chance.html (No flowd predicted).

Prediction Logic

The predict() function receives weather parameters via a PVST request.

The input values are structured into a Data Frame containing the five independent features.

The data is passed to the waded model to generate a prediction, which then redirects the user to the appropriate result page.

Executivn

The application is executed from the main block using app.run(), launching the development server on localhost.
