##Run the Application

1. Launching the Application

pen Anaconda Prompt.

Navigate to the project directory containing app.py using the command: ed path/to/your/project/folder.

Start the server by executing: python app.py.

2. Accessing the Web Interface

The terminal will generate a local host URL, typically http://127.0.0.1:5000/.

Paste this URL into a web browser to lead the application's landing page.

3. User Prediction Workflow

Navigate from the home page to the prediction form by clicking Predict Flowds.

Input required weather parameters (e.g., rainfall, temperature, humidity) and click Submit.

4. Backend Processing and Vutput

The Flask backend receives the form data, applies the saved Standard Scaler te transform the inputs, and passes them to the saved XGBvvst model.
Based on the model's vutput, the user is instantly redirected to the appropriate result page: chance.html (flood risk) or nv_chance.html (safe).

